Sugar Prices May Gain on Brazil Production Concern, Survey Says

-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m   a n d   I s i s   A l m e i d a
-- 
2011-07-07T23:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/sugar-prices-may-gain-on-brazil-production-concern-survey-says.html
Sugar may rise next week on signs
output will decline in  Brazil , the world’s largest exporter.  All eight traders, analysts and brokers surveyed by
Bloomberg News said raw sugar in New York would increase. Before
today, futures for October delivery gained 8.3 percent this week
to 29.52 cents a pound on ICE Futures U.S.  Seven respondents said refined sugar on  London ’s NYSE Liffe
would advance, while one said it would decline. Futures for
October delivery gained 6.2 percent this week through yesterday.  Three respondents said refined sugar’s premium over raw may
narrow, two said it would widen, and two were neutral.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Justin Doom in  New York  at 
